'''Robert Iskandar Ghanem''' (8 May 1942 â€“ 10 February 2019) was a [[Lebanon|Lebanese]] lawyer and politician.

==Early life==
Ghanem hailed from a [[Maronite Christianity in Lebanon|Maronite]] family. He was the son of Lebanese General Iskandar Ghanem.

==Career==
Robert Ghanem was a longtime deputy of the [[National Assembly of Lebanon]] and was the minister of education in the second government of [[Rafic Hariri]].<ref>[http://m.president-2014.com/en/candidates/robert.ghanem Presidential candidates]</ref> Robert Ghanem was a candidate for [[President of Lebanon]] and participated in the [[2014 Lebanese presidential election]].<ref>[http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Lebanon-News/2014/Apr-22/254025-politicians-intensify-deliberations-ahead-of-election.ashx Aoun's bloc to cast blank ballot for presidential election]</ref>

===Views===

Robert Ghanem was a member of the [[March 14 alliance]].<ref>[https://now.mmedia.me/lb/en/president-2014-news/542867-robert-ghanem-seeking-presidency Robert Ghanem seeking presidency]</ref> But nevertheless, Ghanem is viewed{{by whom|date=May 2014}} as a moderate politician with relations across the political spectrum.{{citation needed|date=May 2014}}

==Personal life==
Ghanem was married to the journalist Viviane Haddad since January 23, 1975 and father of two children.<ref>[http://www.robertghanem.com/pages.asp?id=4. biographie]</ref> Ghanem died on 11 February 2019 after a brief illness.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ex-MP Ghanem Dies after Sudden Illness |publisher=Naharnet|work=Naharnet newsdesk|date=10 February 2019|accessdate=11 February 2019|url=http://www.naharnet.com/stories/en/256345-ex-mp-ghanem-dies-after-sudden-illness}}</ref>

